## Case Study: Generative Artificial Intelligence

The **topic of the project** is **Generative Artificial Intelligence (Generative AI)**? fast-evolving technology that is attracting increasing attention from both academia and industry. By analyzing textual data related to Generative AI, this project aims to show how NLP methods can be used to understand how different innovation actors perceive and engage with emerging technologies.

Generative AI, encompassing models capable of producing human-like text, images, code, and more, has gained significant traction across both academic and industrial domains. Its rapid development and widespread adoption have sparked debates on its implications for creativity, productivity, intellectual property, and the future of work. From an Innovation Management perspective, understanding how different actors?esearchers, firms, and policymakers?nterpret and respond to such a transformative technology is both a strategic and analytical challenge.

