## Assignment 1

The dataset was generated by running a query on Scopus with the goal of identifying scientific publications that discuss Generative AI in various forms. The query was executed on **October 16, 2024**, and is as follows:

`TITLE-ABS-KEY("generative artificial intelligent" OR "chat gpt" OR "chatgpt" OR "generative AI" OR "gen AI" OR "natural language generation")`

This search string captures articles that mention Generative AI or related technologies (e.g., ChatGPT, natural language generation) in their **title**, **abstract**, or **keywords** fields.

The resulting dataset is stored in a **CSV file** and includes:

-   The **title**, **abstract**, and **keywords** of each scientific article;

-   **Bibliographic metadata**, such as authors, publication year, source title, and affiliations.

The main goal of this assignment is to **explore and analyze the textual content** of these scientific articles in order to uncover trends, topics, and research focuses related to Generative AI.

To perform the analysis, you can apply a set of Natural Language Processing (NLP) techniques introduced in the previous course modules. The typical workflow includes: (1) Text-Preprocessing (Tokenization, PoS tagging, Stopword removal, Lemmatization or stemming); (2) Keyword extraction; (3)Topic Modeling.

This assignment represents only a first look at the data, aimed at gaining initial insights into how the academic world is discussing Generative AI. It serves as an exploratory step to better understand the landscape before diving into deeper analyses in the following assignments.

```{r}
library(tidyverse)

